content.description: Starts low on crimps and moves up onto better crimps and a nice deep small crimp on the bulge. Go straight up to the point from here on a 2 finger crimp that you crank up onto. Kind of a scary committing top out.
Begin by sitting on one of the talus boulders with hands on the sloping ledge on the right side of the South face. Crux section is the first section of lie-backs. Do not fall off to the right!
content.protection: Gnarly talus and a big drop off make this problem a bit hard to protect. Best to have several pads and spotters; regardless, avoid falling to the right.
content.location: Right side of the South face on lie-back features.

content.description: Same start as the Psychologist V3 only once you hit the crimp on the bulge keep traversing right and throw up for a beautiful jug hold right before the lip. Both variations have been done straight up is slightly easier. The scary part of this climb is mantling the angled slab on the side if you dare.
Short climb with big holds which still need some cleaning. Be careful not to hurt yourself getting off this boulder, downclimb the lichen covered slab and jump to the adjacent boulder to get off.
content.protection: Pads. Best not to fall off in the first place due to butt busting boulders.
content.location: This is on the far left side of the South face of the NQB. Start sitting on one of the big talus boulders.

content.description: Wild problem with an audacious landing. Sit start with hands high on the two good jugs, throw for the sloping side-pull over the lip and hang on for the swing. Crux is holding the swing and not dabbing. Top out is still a bit dirty.
content.protection: Awful landing, stacked pads and spotters are a must.
content.location: The severely overhanging east face of the NQB

content.description: Terrible landings abound on the North Quarry Boulder. The best way down is to down-climb the lichen slab then jump to an adjacent flat boulder.
